  "texts": [
    "Moreover, samples are often collected according to 'convenience', or even synthetically generated by an AI, adding further layers of opacity when compared to a scientifically calibrated survey sampling design.",
    "Second, accuracy.",
    "As the ability of AI polling to correct for sample biases increases, the polling industry is incentivised to 'push the boundary', and depend on ever 'riskier' (under-powered, unrepresentative, cheaper, etc.) samples.",
    "While this behaviour may eventually converge to a stable equilibrium of accepted methodologies, the rush towards biased samples poses a meaningful threat to the short-and medium-term accuracy of published AI polls, which can have adverse effect on electoral choice.",
    "The most important issue with holding AI pollsters accountable lies in the ability to explain AI polling models."
  ],
